      "title": "Hybrid Work and Urban Life",
      "text": "Many firms now allow staff to work remotely two or three days a week. Supporters argue that commuting less reduces stress and carbon emissions. However, city-centre cafés and shops report fewer customers on weekdays. Some economists believe hybrid models may gradually rebalance urban economies if public transport investment keeps pace."
    },
